The paper discusses the use of multidimensional persistent homology for shape comparison in computer vision and computer graphics applications, indicating that cs.CG and cs.CV are likely categories. The paper also involves the development of a stability preserving method for comparing rank invariants of vector functions obtained from discrete data, suggesting that cs.DS and cs.NA are also possible categories. Finally, the numerical tests mentioned in the abstract suggest that cs.SI (Scientific Computing) could also be a relevant category.
